According to a report by Intel Market Research, the Europe Logistics Market was valued at USD 345.6 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 367.5 billion in 2025 to USD 498.7 billion by 2030, registering a CAGR of 6.3% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust growth driven by the rapid expansion of e-commerce, increasing adoption of digital logistics platforms, warehouse automation, and the growing need for efficient transportation and supply chain management. Investments in AI-powered route optimization, IoT-enabled shipment tracking, and sustainable logistics practices are enabling companies to improve operational efficiency while meeting evolving customer expectations for faster and more reliable deliveries.
